23 section more than three years after the date on which the [debt management service provider] reg-
24 istrant or person enters into an agreement for a debt management service or debt resolution
25 service with the consumer that suffered the ascertainable loss of money or property or more than
26 three years after the [debt management service provider] registrant or person performs a debt man-
27 agement service that violates ORS 697.652 or a debt resolution service that violates section 14
28 of this 2026 Act. An action under this section may be commenced within three years after the
29 transaction that is the subject of the action or within two years after the facts on which the action
30 is based were or should have been discovered, but an action may not be commenced more than five
31 years after the transaction. Failure to commence an action on a timely basis is an affirmative de-
32 fense.
